# Plugin Template Compliance

This repo is a **single-plugin** Cursor plugin at the repo root. See `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` for the full contribution guide. Canonical spec: https://github.com/cursor/plugin-template.

## Structure — hard rules

- Plugin name (`.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` → `name`) matches `^[a-z0-9](?:[a-z0-9.-]*[a-z0-9])?$`.
- MCP server definitions live **only** in `mcp.json` at repo root. Never rename this file.
- Hook definitions live **only** in `hooks/hooks.json`. Hook scripts live in `scripts/`.
- Every referenced path (logo, hook `command`, skill assets) is a **safe relative path** — no `..`, no absolute paths.
- Logo is committed to `assets/` and referenced by relative path in `plugin.json`.
- No `.cursor-plugin/marketplace.json` — this repo is single-plugin, not a marketplace.
- No `plugins/` subdirectory — this repo is single-plugin.

## Frontmatter — strict

- `rules/*.mdc` — YAML frontmatter with `description`.
- `skills/*/SKILL.md` — YAML frontmatter with `name` + `description`. `name` matches the directory.
- Agents (`agents/*.md`), commands (`commands/*.(md|mdc|markdown|txt)`) — `name` + `description`.
- Frontmatter opens with `---\n` and closes with `\n---\n`. Missing keys fail the validator.

## Skills

- Path: `skills/<kebab-case>/SKILL.md`.
- Use only the Harness MCP v2 consolidated tools: `harness_list`, `harness_get`, `harness_create`, `harness_update`, `harness_delete`, `harness_execute`, `harness_search`, `harness_describe`, `harness_schema`, `harness_diagnose`, `harness_status`.
- Required sections: `## Instructions`, `## Examples`, `## Performance Notes`, `## Troubleshooting`.
- Every new skill gets a row in the README skill table.

## Hooks

- Event names come from https://cursor.com/docs/agent/hooks — do not invent. Commonly used here: `beforeMCPExecution`, `afterMCPExecution`.
- Matchers for MCP tools use `MCP:<tool_name>` format (e.g. `MCP:harness_create|MCP:harness_update`).
- Scripts read JSON from stdin, write JSON to stdout.
- **Fail open** — on missing credentials, malformed stdin, network failure, or any exception, emit `{"permission":"allow"}` (for `before*`) or `{}` (for `after*`). Wrap `main()` in `try/catch`. Never block the agent because of our bug.
- `.mjs` with `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang and executable bit set. Zero npm dependencies — Node standard library only.
- Scope narrowly by inspecting `tool_input.resource_type`; bail early on unrelated calls.

## Environment & Secrets

- Scripts inherit env from Cursor. Required: `HARNESS_API_KEY`, `HARNESS_ACCOUNT_ID`. Optional: `HARNESS_BASE_URL`, `HARNESS_ORG`, `HARNESS_PROJECT`.
- Never commit `.env`, API keys, or account IDs. Never log credentials to stdout.
- Network calls must time out (10s default via `scripts/harness-api.mjs`).

## Sync when you change

- New MCP tool → update `rules/harness.mdc` catalog AND the README tool table.
- New skill → update the README skill table.
- New hook → update the README Governance Hooks table AND `rules/harness.mdc`.
- Any shipped change → bump `version` in `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.

## Before you commit

1. `node scripts/validate-plugin.mjs` — runs syntax, frontmatter, manifest, hook-executable, mcp.json shape checks. CI (`.github/workflows/validate.yml`) runs the same on every PR.
2. Smoke-test hooks with synthetic stdin and unset credentials — confirm fail-open (CI does this too).
3. Update README if the user-facing surface changed.

## Never

- Rename `mcp.json`, `hooks/hooks.json`, or `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.
- Reference paths outside the plugin root.
- Weaken fail-open behavior in hooks.
- Convert to a multi-plugin layout.
- Add npm runtime dependencies to hook scripts.
- Use undocumented Cursor hook event names.
